     <h2>Committee Report on the Petition of Gyles Merrill</h2>
     
     <div class="docbody">
      
      <p>10 April 1771. <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ manuscript ]">MS</abbr> not found. Prepared by a committee appointed and reporting the same day, composed of <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>, Samuel Batcheller, and John Noyes.</p>
      <p>Gyles Merrill, pastor of the First Church of Plaistow, N.H. (formerly the Second Church of Haverhill, Mass.), sought the legislatures consent to an offer from the Haverhill parish to grant him his parsonage in fee simple. The committees report, described as recommending That a Bill be brot in to enable the North Precinct in Haverhill, to grant the Premises described in the Petition . . . notwithstanding any former Vote or Votes of the Town or Proprietors of Haverhill, was approved. Batcheller was <span class="pb" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-01-02-pb-0248">[248<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-01/ADMS-06-01-02-pb-0248.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>ordered to prepare the bill (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Journals of the House of Representatives of Massachusetts&lt;/i&gt; [[1715]], Boston, reprinted by the Massachusetts Historical Society, 1919. (For the years for which reprints are not yet available, the original printings are cited, by year and session.) ]">Mass., <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">House Jour.</span></span>, 17701771, p. 201). For the bill adopted in response to the committees recommendations, see <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;The Acts and Resolves, Public and Private, of the Province of the Massachusetts Bay&lt;/i&gt;, Boston, 18691922; 21 vols. ]">Mass., <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Province Laws</span></span>, 5:121, with Merrills petition at p. 145146.</p>
     </div>
    </div><div class="citation_box"><div><span class="bold">Cite as: </span> 
